element.name: CRITERIA
element.documentation: Specifies this class's attributes are to be used in criteria queries.

element.name: ENTITY
element.documentation: Denotes this class is to be treated as a persistable entity.

element.name: SERVICE
element.documentation: Denotes this class represents a service that is implemented using the facade pattern.

element.name: FINDER_METHOD
element.documentation: Denotes this operation to perform a query on the underlying collection of entities, rather than execute business logic.

element.name: IDENTIFIER
element.documentation: Explicitly specifies this attribute to make up the entity's identifier (primary key)

element.name: UNIQUE
element.documentation: Denotes an attribute to be unique among all possible instances of the underlying entity. In UML2, the attribute 'Unique' property=true has the same effect. Deprecated: Use UML2 unique flag instead.

element.name: VALUE_OBJECT
element.documentation: Denotes a class to be a simple class that is only holding values and providing accessors to them.

element.name: EXCEPTION
element.documentation: This class will instruct the generation of an exception class.

element.name: APPLICATION_EXCEPTION
element.documentation: This class will instruct the generation of a checked exception class.

element.name: UNEXPECTED_EXCEPTION
element.documentation: This class will instruct the generation of an unchecked exception class.

element.name: EXCEPTION_REF
element.documentation: Indicates that the target is an exception which is thrown by the method. Deprecated: In UML2, design the operation to throw the declared exceptions instead of drawing a dependency.

element.name: ENUMERATION
element.documentation: This class will instruct the generation of a type-safe enumeration class. Deprecated: Use UML Enumeration types instead of the stereotype. Deprecated: Use UML Enumeration instead.

element.name: WEBSERVICE
element.documentation: Denotes a class to represent a collection of web service operations, similar behavior as a normal Service.

element.name: WEBSERVICE_OPERATION
element.documentation: Denotes an operation to be exposed as a web service.

element.name: WEB_FAULT
element.documentation: Denotes an exception thrown by a CXF or JAX-WS webservice operation.

element.name: XMLSCHEMA
element.documentation: Denotes a package whose contents will be output as an XML Schema file. Used by XML and WebService cartridges.

element.name: NULLABLE
element.documentation: Indicates a service operation argument may be left unspecified (eg. Java null). Deprecated: Use the parameter multiplicity lowerBound=0 instead.

element.name: TRANSIENT
element.documentation: Indicates the attribute or association end should not be persisted/serialized.

element.name: MANAGEABLE
element.documentation: Only makes sense when there already is an Entity stereotype. Add this one to manage this entity through all 3 tiers.

element.name: FRONT_END_EXCEPTION
element.documentation: Modeled on a transition within a front-end process, it designates an exception occurring while processing an action.

element.name: FRONT_END_COMPONENT
element.documentation: This stereotype is modeled on an class to denote it is representing a view on a front end component.

element.name: FRONT_END_VIEW
element.documentation: This stereotype is modeled on an action state to denote it is representing a view on a front end (such as a JSP page).

element.name: FRONT_END_USE_CASE
element.documentation: A use-case that participates in the front-end (or presentation-tier) processes.

element.name: FRONT_END_APPLICATION
element.documentation: The use-case flagged with this stereotype will be the application's starting point, you can only use this stereotype in combination with the <<FrontEndUseCase>> stereotype.

element.name: QUEUE
element.documentation: The node flagged with this stereotype represents a Queue message destination (i.e. JMS, etc).

element.name: TOPIC
element.documentation: The node flagged with this stereotype represents a Topic message destination (i.e. JMS, etc).

element.name: DOC_ONLY
element.documentation: Modeled component is for documentation only. Do not generate code.

element.name: FUTURE
element.documentation: Modeled component will be developed in the Future. Do not generate code.

element.name: IGNORE
element.documentation: Modeled component should be ignored. Do not generate code.

element.name: ANALYSIS
element.documentation: Modeled component is part of an RUP analysis package. Do not generate code.

element.name: PERSPECTIVE
element.documentation: Modeled component is part of an RUP perspective package. Do not generate code.

element.name: ANNOTATION_TYPE
element.documentation: Modeled component is an annotation.

element.name: GENERIC
element.documentation: Modeled component is an annotation.

element.name: MODEL_HYPERLINK
element.documentation: Represents a hyperlink within a model

element.name: EXTERNAL_HYPERLINK
element.documentation: Represents an external hyperlink (i.e. to an external website for example).

element.name: PERSISTENCE_SCHEMA
element.documentation: The name of the persistence schema that contains the table.

allowedValues.value: A string representing the name of the database schema where the entity will be persisted

element.name: PERSISTENCE_TABLE
element.documentation: The name of the table corresponding to this entity in the persistent store. If unspecified, the table name is the upper-underscore version of the Entity name.

element.name: PERSISTENCE_COLUMN
element.documentation: The name of the column corresponding to this property in the persistent store. If unspecified, the column name is the upper-underscore version of the Entity property name.

element.name: PERSISTENCE_COLUMN_LENGTH
element.documentation: Default if unspecified = 25. Applies to String values only.

element.name: PERSISTENCE_COLUMN_INDEX
element.documentation: The index to create on the property column

element.name: COLUMN_UNIQUE_GROUP
element.documentation: The name of the unique constraint group to which this unique attribute belongs

element.name: PERSISTENCE_FOREIGN_IDENTIFIER
element.documentation: Default=false. If true, the same Entity identifier values for this FK will also be used for the associated Entity PK

element.name: PERSISTENCE_ASSIGNED_IDENTIFIER
element.documentation: Default=true: Create an assigned identifier attribute for the entity if no attributes are designated as identifier attributes.

element.name: PERSISTENCE_FOREIGN_KEY_CONSTRAINT_NAME
element.documentation: The name of the foreign key corresponding to this relation in the persistent store.

element.name: PERSISTENCE_IMMUTABLE
element.documentation: Denotes this entity's property can only be set at construction time.

element.name: PERSISTENCE_JOINCOLUMN_ORDER
element.documentation: For ManyToOne associations, the order of the @JoinColumn annotations in the composite PK MUST match the order of the columns in the FK definition. The JoinColumn order should be the same as the order of columns in the Primary Key of the Entity.

element.name: PERSISTENCE_ENUMERATION_MEMBER_VARIABLE
element.documentation: Specifies whether the enumeration attribute is defined as a member variable rather than a literal. This should only be set if the attribute is NOT a literal. Deprecated: Use UML Enumerations instead.

element.name: PERSISTENCE_ENUMERATION_LITERAL_PARAMETERS
element.documentation: Specifies the enumeration literal parameters which are passed to the appropriate constructor when created. The parameters are comma separated. Deprecated: Use UML Enumerations instead.

element.name: PERSISTENCE_ASSOCIATION_END_PRIMARY
element.documentation: Indicates whether or not the association end is considered "primary", to indicate which side of a one-to-one or many-to-many association should get the foreign key (be the relationship owner).

element.name: ASSOCIATION_END_UNIQUE_GROUP
element.documentation: The name of the unique constraint group to which this unique association end belongs

element.name: PRESENTATION_CONTROLLER_USECASE
element.documentation: The value should correspond to the use-case holding the activity graph which has this controller as its context. This is used when deferring operations to the controller. Please note that if your CASE tool supports setting the context of an activity graph you will not need to explicitly set this tagged value. This feature has been provided to support tool such as Poseidon that have only limited UML support. If you are a MagicDraw user you will not need to use this tagged value, instead assign the controller by right clicking on it and selecting "Assign...".

element.name: PRESENTATION_REST_PATH
element.documentation: Some presentation layers have built in rest controllers.

element.name: PRESENTATION_SUBSTITUTION_NAME
element.documentation: Some presentation layers have built in rest controllers.

element.name: PRESENTATION_SUBMIT_ACTION
element.documentation: Some presentation layers have built in rest controllers.

element.name: PRESENTATION_IF
element.documentation: Some presentation layers have built in rest controllers.

element.name: PRESENTATION_COMPONENT
element.documentation: Some presentation layers have built in rest controllers.

element.name: PRESENTATION_COMPONENT_MAPPED_MODEL
element.documentation: Some presentation layers have built in rest controllers.

element.name: PRESENTATION_PATH
element.documentation: File path for this presentation.

element.name: PRESENTATION_FILENAME
element.documentation: Presentation file name.

element.name: PRESENTATION_TARGETURL
element.documentation: Target URL for this presentation item

element.name: PRESENTATION_ACCESS_ROLES
element.documentation: Roles allowed to access this presentation item.

element.name: PRESENTATION_EXTRA_ROUTES
element.documentation: Extra routes for either the usecase or view.

element.name: PRESENTATION_USECASE_ACTIVITY
element.documentation: For tools that do not allow the placement of activity graphs inside of a use-case you can use this tagged value to point to an activity graph, this will link them and denotes that the graphs specifies this use-case.

element.name: PRESENTATION_ICON
element.documentation: The icon to be used for this item (Use Case, Action and View)

element.name: PRESENTATION_GENERATE_TABLE
element.documentation: The icon to be used for this item (Use Case, Action and View)

element.name: PRESENTATION_COMPONENT_BEAN_NAME
element.documentation: Component bean name

element.name: PRESENTATION_COMPONENT_TABLE_NAME
element.documentation: Component bean name

element.name: PRESENTATION_TABLE_COLUMNS
element.documentation: The collection will be displayed in scrollable tabular format. Each column in this table will be mapped to a property of the object type contained in the collection. So you will need to make sure all objects have accessor methods for the property you list in this tagged value. Properties are separated using a comma ','. More than one value maybe be assigned to this tag, all properties will correctly be resolved.
element.appliedOnElement: A collection type parameter going into an action state carrying the <<FrontEndView>> stereotype

element.name: PRESENTATION_IS_TABLE
element.documentation: A flag indicating whether or not a parameter should be considered a table. This must be set to true when you wish to display a list of simple types (such as strings) within a table.
element.appliedOnElement: A collection type parameter going into an action state carrying the <<FrontEndView>> stereotype

element.name: SERIALVERSION_UID
element.documentation: The serialVersionUID value to put on an Entity

element.name: MANAGEABLE_DISPLAY_NAME
element.documentation: The column representing this entity,by default the first <<Unique>> attribute found is taken but you might want to specify another column yourself. This value is used when one entity has a foreign key to another one and you want to select the value of this foreign key from a combo-box and you would like to see a more meaningful label for each option, if no <<Unique>> attribute is found the identifier is used, which isn't very helpful.

allowedValues.value: any column name present in this entity
the name of the identifier column

element.name: ANNOTATION_TYPE_RETENTION
element.documentation: Annotation type retention.

element.name: ANNOTATION_TYPE_TARGET
element.documentation: Annotation type target.

element.name: ANNOTATION_TYPE_DOCUMENTED
element.documentation: Annotation type documented

element.name: ANDROMDA_ADDITIONAL_ANNOTATION
element.documentation: Annotation type extra annotation

element.name: ANDROMDA_GENERIC_TYPES
element.documentation: Annotation generic types

element.name: ANDROMDA_GENERIC_PARAMETERS
element.documentation: Annotation generic parameter types

element.name: ANDROMDA_ADDITIONAL_EXTENDS
element.documentation: Annotation type for external classes that must be extended

element.name: ANDROMDA_ADDITIONAL_IMPLEMENTS
element.documentation: Annotation type for external interfaces that must be extended

element.name: ANDROMDA_OPERATION_TEST_NAME
element.documentation: Annotation type for external interfaces that must be extended

element.name: ANDROMDA_OPERATION_TEST_DISPLAY_NAME
element.documentation: Annotation type for external interfaces that must be extended

element.documentation: Deprecated: Use UML2 unordered non-unique 1:M relationship instead

element.name: LIST_TYPE

element.name: SET_TYPE

element.name: ORDERED_SET_TYPE
element.documentation: Deprecated: Use UML2 ordered unique 1:M relationship instead

element.name: PRESENTATION_CLASS
element.documentation: CSS class name for web frontend.

element.name: PRESENTATION_FORM_ENCTYPE
element.documentation: Enc type for forms

element.name: WEB_VIEW_MIN
element.documentation: Minimum value of a front end field

element.name: WEB_VIEW_MAX
element.documentation: Maximum field of a front end field
